1
00:01:23,320 --> 00:01:25,200
This is the 'Song of the Volga Boatmen'.

2
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:26,600
It portrays the working-class people

3
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:27,840
oppressed by the Tsar,

4
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:29,240
yet striving to survive.

5
00:01:29,880 --> 00:01:30,680
No wonder.

6
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:32,880
Hearing this song

7
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:35,009
reminds me of our current life.

8
00:01:36,240 --> 00:01:37,520
These damn invaders,

9
00:01:38,360 --> 00:01:39,479
and the Tsar who oppressed the people back then,

10
00:01:39,479 --> 00:01:40,810
what's the difference?

11
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:21,680
Good.

12
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:23,480
Encore! Great!

13
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:25,440
Encore!

14
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:28,280
Encore!

15
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:30,760
Encore!

16
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:33,160
Encore!

17
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:35,360
Then I'll play another song for everyone,

18
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:36,600
'Riding the Wind and Waves'.

19
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:37,280
Great.

20
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,920
We should let the Japanese

21
00:02:38,920 --> 00:02:40,600
hear this song too.

22
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,240
Yes, great!

23
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:52,480
Wait.

24
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,520
Miss Qin.

25
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:00,680
Xiaoxiong.

26
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:03,040
The song 'Riding the Wind and Waves' is controversial.

27
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:04,300
We won't play it today.

28
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:09,880
Welcome everyone

29
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:12,320
to our harmonica club's open-air concert.

30
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:15,320
Our harmonica club was founded by a German,

31
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:16,800
Mr. Schiller.

32
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:18,920
Our mission is

33
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:21,180
to welcome all music-loving friends

34
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:23,240
to learn the harmonica at our club.

35
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:25,800
Music gives people armor

36
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:28,680
to withstand life's pressures and blows.

37
00:03:29,079 --> 00:03:31,540
It also allows you to enjoy the beauty of life

38
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:33,680
and create a bright future.

39
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:36,600
It can also become your life companion,

40
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,260
accompanying you throughout your life.

41
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:45,240
When words fail,

42
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:47,920
music speaks.

43
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:50,280
Next, we bring you a

44
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:51,600
joyful piece,

45
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,240
'Ode to Joy'.

46
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:07,000
Business is booming lately, Boss Shen.

47
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:07,860
What good stuff

48
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:09,120
is loaded in the back?

49
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:20,240
Just some samples for the firm.

50
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,700
Come on, let's take a look.

51
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:23,920
Why check Boss Shen's goods?

52
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:25,050
There's no need.

53
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:27,800
Thank you, Section Chief Qian.

54
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:30,000
I'll get going if there's nothing else.

55
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:31,400
Boss Shen, actually,

56
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:33,040
I have a favor to ask you.

57
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:33,680
Tell me.

58
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:35,570
I don't know if Chen Yu told you.

59
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:36,280
About what?

60
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:40,890
Zhu Tianyou from the Gendarmerie.

61
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:45,280
I remember now.

62
00:04:46,159 --> 00:04:47,620
About that killer, right?

63
00:04:47,840 --> 00:04:50,640
Believe it or not, I actually asked around for you.

64
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:51,940
I heard that person

65
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:53,680
is missing his

66
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:54,560
left pinky.

67
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,080
And he killed Japanese

68
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:57,280
in Fangzheng County.

69
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:58,720
No, how tall is he?

70
00:04:58,920 --> 00:05:00,920
What does he look like? How old is he?

71
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:02,320
I don't know about that.

72
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:04,280
Don't worry.

73
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:06,240
I'll go to Chairman Wang's place later

74
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:08,400
and ask him to ask around for you.

75
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:10,600
Chairman Wang is great.

76
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,040
He knows a lot of people in the underworld.

77
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:13,360
He might find something out.

78
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:14,490
He definitely will.

79
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:15,640
Okay, I'll go now.

80
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:18,080
What's wrong now?

81
00:05:32,159 --> 00:05:33,400
What are you doing?

82
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:35,640
Buy something for Mr. Wang,

83
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,880
and say it's a token of my appreciation.

84
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:38,800
Buying things for him,

85
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:40,130
I shouldn't let you pay.

86
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:41,920
Take it, Mr. Shen.

87
00:05:41,960 --> 00:05:43,800
Otherwise I won't feel at ease.

88
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:46,480
Got it.

89
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:47,760
Got it.

90
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:50,170
Don't worry.

91
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:51,520
My stuff

92
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:53,450
is definitely worth the money.

93
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:54,600
Okay.

94
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:55,440
Wait for my news.

95
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:56,240
Got it.

96
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:04,400
Captain Matsuda, what brings you here?

97
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:05,160
I came to see

98
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:07,840
what's going on here.

99
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:09,120
Let me introduce you.

100
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,800
This is Mr. Shen from Datong Trading Company.

101
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,600
We do a lot of business together,

102
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,460
and he's Chen Yu's older brother.

103
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,640
This is our dear

104
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:16,800
Captain Matsuda.

105
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:17,920
Captain Matsuda.

106
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:19,540
I've heard a lot about you.

107
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:24,400
What's in the car?

108
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:27,410
Some samples from my trading company.

109
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:28,280
Open it.

110
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,080
Sister Qin,

111
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:34,320
why did you stop us from playing "Pioneers" just now?

112
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:36,380
Did you see the audience's reaction?

113
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,060
The light in their eyes

114
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:39,480
is hope.

115
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:43,610
Drink some water first.

116
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:44,880
Sister Qin,

117
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:48,290
now is the time to strike while the iron is hot.

118
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:49,760
Come here.

119
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,280
Sit down.

120
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,690
You saw Li San today too.

121
00:06:58,600 --> 00:06:59,480
The way he looked at us

122
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:00,680
was like eyeing prey.

123
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:02,370
He's already targeting us.

124
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:04,880
So the upcoming performances

125
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:05,940
must be suspended.

126
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:08,680
Xiaoxiong.

127
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:12,080
The Japanese are watching any signs of anti-Japanese resistance

128
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:13,200
very closely.

129
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:15,240
That's exactly why they're watching so closely.

130
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,240
We need to let more people

131
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:17,280
hear our music.

132
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:19,560
Outdoor performances have a limited reach.

133
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:21,120
Think about how wide a radio audience could be.

134
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,200
How many times have we contacted

135
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:23,320
Kong Xuzhou from the broadcasting station?

136
00:07:23,320 --> 00:07:24,320
They are a commercial radio station,

137
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:25,360
not controlled by the Japanese.

138
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:26,320
Playing there

139
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:28,410
can let more people hear our music.

140
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:31,360
Even if the broadcasting station is independent in name,

141
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:33,560
can they really avoid their eyes and ears?

142
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:35,960
Going there now is like throwing ourselves into a trap.

143
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:37,440
Our music is the bullet,

144
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:39,560
and the broadcasting station is the best gun barrel.

145
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:40,600
If we don't do this,

146
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,480
we can't turn our harmonica club

147
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:43,080
into the second gun of anti-Japanese resistance.

148
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:45,159
Our club's anti-Japanese propaganda requires strategy

149
00:07:45,159 --> 00:07:46,159
and the right timing.

150
00:07:46,159 --> 00:07:47,240
If we go now

151
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,720
and the Japanese target us, what then?

152
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:50,180
The club will be finished.

153
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,840
Sister Qin, if we keep hiding like this,

154
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:53,520
when will we ever drive the Japanese out?

155
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:54,960
The broadcasting station is a rare opportunity.

156
00:07:54,960 --> 00:07:57,680
If we miss this, who knows how long we'll have to wait.

157
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,540
Think about it.

158
00:07:59,159 --> 00:08:00,800
Those working in the factories,

159
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:02,400
those farming in the fields.

160
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,200
They can't see the outdoor concert,

161
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:05,840
but they can hear the radio broadcast.

162
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:06,760
We need to let them know

163
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:08,480
there are still people fighting for this land,

164
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:10,610
so they won't continue to stay silent.

165
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:13,920
Xiaoxiong,

166
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:15,480
I know what you're going to say.

167
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:17,080
I understand your thoughts.

168
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,440
But right now,

169
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:21,040
I can't risk your safety and the safety of the team.

170
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,880
The banner of the Harmonica Society cannot fall.

171
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:23,940
So we can only wait.

172
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:25,960
We can't wait anymore, Sister Qin.

173
00:08:25,960 --> 00:08:26,920
Every day, our compatriots

174
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,580
are being killed and bullied.

175
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:29,960
If we wait one more day,

176
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:31,730
there will be more despair.

177
00:08:35,919 --> 00:08:37,450
The broadcasting station.

178
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,320
We must go.

179
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,039
Gu Xiaoxiong,

180
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:47,080
if you insist on going,

181
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:49,250
can you bear the consequences?

182
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:55,100
I have to bear them even if I can't.

183
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,640
We formed the Harmonica Society

184
00:08:57,640 --> 00:08:58,970
to resist the invaders.

185
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:38,440
Captain Matsuda,

186
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:40,360
this is a special Bizen ware black pottery

187
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:43,760
I got from Bizen City, Okayama Prefecture.

188
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:45,680
It's very rare.

189
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:48,140
The glaze color will change with the tea.

190
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,000
Interesting.

191
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:50,000
Do you like it?

192
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:54,000
A Bizen ware black pottery tea set

193
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:55,090
is too precious.

194
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:56,360
I can't accept it.

195
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:58,080
You might have misunderstood.

196
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,560
This is not a gift from me.

197
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,800
Chief Qian asked me to buy it for you.

198
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:07,440
Isn't that right, Boss Shen? I...

199
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:07,920
Look,

200
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,530
Chief Qian is embarrassed.

201
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:11,080
Actually,

202
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:14,120
he even paid for it.

203
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:15,600
If you don't like it,

204
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:17,880
my business deal will fall through.

205
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:20,400
Boss Shen,

206
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:22,240
you're very good at doing business.

207
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,100
You flatter me.

208
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:26,160
Captain Matsuda,

209
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:27,840
if there's nothing else, I'll get going.

210
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:29,700
President Wang is waiting for me.

211
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:32,420
Are you friends with President Wang?

212
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,700
We've been friends for over 20 years.

213
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:38,920
Thank you.

214
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:40,720
Boss Shen,

215
00:10:40,920 --> 00:10:41,600
thank you.

216
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:42,920
Take care.

217
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:45,040
Let them pass.

218
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:24,920
Hold the harmonicas in your hands when we take the picture.

219
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:25,520
Come on.

220
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,640
Alright, everyone,

221
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:30,900
we're getting ready to take the picture.

222
00:12:41,840 --> 00:12:42,920
Thanks for your hard work.

223
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:43,760
Go up those stairs.

224
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:44,400
I know.

225
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:52,040
Brother,

226
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:53,460
why are you so late?

227
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:56,400
President Wang had something to do, so I was delayed.

228
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:58,200
I didn't delay your plans, did I?

229
00:12:58,240 --> 00:12:59,040
Brother Shen.

230
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:00,080
Look,

231
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:01,840
is this the only thing missing?

232
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:02,320
Heming,

233
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:03,080
check it.

234
00:13:07,040 --> 00:13:08,280
Yes, this is it.

235
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:10,770
Just in time. Let's install it right away.

236
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:14,280
Thank you, Brother Shen.

237
00:13:14,280 --> 00:13:15,520
You and Lingzi go back first.

238
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:16,450
Leave this to me.

239
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:18,960
Come here.

240
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:24,000
I'll leave Ajin here.

241
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:25,760
Tell him if you have any problems.

242
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:27,040
I will help you solve them.

243
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:28,640
Don't push yourselves too hard.

244
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:29,770
Okay, Brother Shen.

245
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:31,000
We'll be leaving now.

246
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:31,440
Okay.

247
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:32,160
Be careful.

248
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:33,160
Lingzi, let's go.

249
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:34,120
Okay.

250
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:35,400
Be careful.

251
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:37,100
You guys go back first.

252
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:45,770
It's installed.

253
00:13:45,880 --> 00:13:47,940
I will notify you when to activate it.

254
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:50,480
Close the gate as soon as the three minutes are up.

255
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:51,200
Be careful.

256
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:52,050
Understood.

257
00:13:54,680 --> 00:13:55,480
Sir, sir.

258
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,280
Tonight's performance was great.

259
00:13:57,280 --> 00:13:58,140
Thank you, sir.

260
00:13:58,680 --> 00:13:59,360
Not bad.

261
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:00,840
Go to bed early, sir.

262
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:06,320
Don't move. Don't move.

263
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:08,090
Behave yourselves.

264
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:10,400
Don't move. Don't move.

265
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,440
Stand still and behave.

266
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:19,800
Mr. Gu.

267
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:21,160
Long time no see.

268
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:23,100
What are you doing?

269
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:26,800
The broadcasting station's 'Trailblazer' was played well.

270
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:30,640
Please play it again at the Special Service Department.

271
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:33,220
Take them all away.

272
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:34,520
Let go.

273
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,730
How dare you resist arrest?

274
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:37,680
Beat him up.

275
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:40,000
Don't move. Stop.

276
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:44,480
Stop.

277
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:48,140
Move. Behave yourselves.

278
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:51,960
Take them away.
